gomodel:SYNGO_1934  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Cbln1 interferes with synaptogenesis induced by NL1(-) but not by LRRTM2 by competing with NRX1β(S4+)\"\nFig.2: \"Cbln1 specifically binds to NRXs carrying the splice site 4 insert.\"\nFig.3: \"Cbln1 binds to NRX1β(S4+) under low Ca2+ conditions\"\n\n20/11/2017 Pim\n- The isoform of Nrx1beta was traced back to xxxx via PMID:16624946 using aa sequence 'GNND-NERLAIARQRIPYRLGRVVDEWLLDK' in blast search. This resulted 100% hits against reviewed Neurexin-1-beta sequences in rat (Q63373), mouse (P0DI97) and human (P58400).. Experimental description: \"Mixed cerebellar cultures were prepared from embryonic day 17 to day-of-birth ICR or cbln1-null mice as previously described (Matsuda et al., 2009).\" p. 1448\n\n20/11/2017 Pim\n- Species of the overexpressed protein was not stated in the paper. Authors were contacted for this information (myuzaki@a5.keio.jp). Author responded:\n\n\"Thank you for your inquiry.\n\nThe Neurexin-1 beta cDNA was from mouse. Similarly, Neurexin-2 beta and -3 beta cDNAs are from mouse.\n\nWith best wishes,\n\nMichi\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1934" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

